The paper focuses on image recognition using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to identify artworks viewed by visitors in museum spaces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the practical and technical challenges in devising a robust system for recognizing artworks viewed by visitors, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of wearable cameras to capture images of artworks viewed by visitors could also fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the applicability of the system to engage audiences with museum exhibitions, which could fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of CNNs for artwork identification could also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
